\par\pard\plain \ri-1600\sb240\sl260\slmult0\qj\ltrch\loch {\f4\fs28\b1\i1\ul\ulc0\cf4\cb2\highlight2 HN3}{\f1\fs28\b0\i0\cf1  An EEOC guideline, dealing with the problem of an employee who refuses to work during an employer's normal workweek due to his religion, declares that an employer has an obligation under the statute to accommodate to the reasonable religious needs of employees where such accommodation can be made without serious inconvenience to the conduct of the business.  }{\f6\fs28\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf4\cb2\highlight2 29 C.F.R. \loch\af6\hich\af6\dbch\af6\uc1\u167\'A7 1605.1 (1967)}{\f1\fs28\b0\i0\cf1 .}
