\par\pard\plain \ri-1600\sb240\sl260\slmult0\qj\ltrch\loch {\f4\fs28\b1\i1\ul\ulc0\cf4\cb2\highlight2 HN7}{\f1\fs28\b0\i0\cf1  The paramount concern of Congress in enacting Title VII, }{\f6\fs28\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf4\cb2\highlight2 42 U.S.C.S. \loch\af6\hich\af6\dbch\af6\uc1\u167\'A7 2000e-2}{\f1\fs28\b0\i0\cf1 , was the elimination of discrimination in employment. In the absence of clear statutory language or legislative history to the contrary, the U.S. Supreme Court will not readily construe the statute to require an employer to discriminate against some employees in order to enable others to observe their Sabbath.}
\par\pard\plain \ri-1600\sb240\sl340\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f3\fs28\b1\i0\cf1 Lawyers' Edition Display}
